      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some influencers promote \"loading doses,\" these high doses still carry risks, even over just a few weeks, of Vitamin D toxicity. The concept of a \"safe\" threshold varies, and what feels fine to some can be harmful to others without lab testing. Since you are looking for a fast fix, consulting a doctor first is the only way to ensure the dosage is actually necessary and safe for your body chemistry. It is always best to prioritize proven medical advice over social media recommendations for supplements.",
      "source": "target",
