      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even with careful timing or taking it with fat, extremely high short-term doses still carry a risk of hypercalcemia, which is dangerous. There is no established, universally safe protocol for administering massive doses like 50,000 IU without blood work monitoring. Because Vitamin D toxicity can build up over time, stopping after two weeks might not immediately reverse any potential damage. Please let a healthcare provider guide you on safe and effective supplementation for winter blues.",
      "source": "target",
